Job Description:
This IT Web Designer/Developer position serves on the ITCS Enterprise Information Systems team as a technical resource and supports the web development needs of the university.
This position develops custom solutions to enhance the functionality of applications to meet unique customer needs. Employee should be comfortable developing plugins, themes, custom post types, WordPress CLI scripts, and other WordPress CMS solutions based on project requirements. This position is responsible for assessing and triaging bugs and enhancements that come into GitHub as well as participating in all stages of development, testing, implementation, and maintenance. Furthermore, this position must be able to work with standard web interfaces (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and a full application stack consisting of server OS, web server (IIS and Apache), programming and scripting (PHP, Python), and database (MySQL and MSSQL). Experience using GitHub for version control and documentation is preferred.
This position is responsible for application administration, advanced troubleshooting and support, and developing enhancements for various enterprise web applications. Additionally, this position offers advanced technical expertise to consultants and clients for enterprise applications in a wide variety of areas which requires an overall understanding of the ECU technology infrastructure. Employee will assist with determining the best solutions for campus users to meet unique needs and troubleshoot issues.
This position helps in the selection of applications and creation of standards and guidelines for its proper use and configuration to meet the needs of customers. Employee is responsible for creating tools using vendor APIs and web services to extend application functionality for our users. In addition, this position is responsible for data management from outside resources importing into a variety of enterprise applications. Employee serves as an expert in the use of these applications and should keep up to date on application upgrades and new features.
The position should to stay up to date on new technologies, best practices, and modern development methods. Employee will communicate regularly with peers using chat, audio, and video. Employees are required to adjust their standard work schedule to meet the requirements of their position, which includes and not limited to evening and weekend hours to perform scheduled and unscheduled workload requirements to maintain University operations.
